# Everything under macos/ is consumed on macOS. Pin LF in the working tree on
# every platform.
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS: this repo is authored on Windows with
# core.autocrlf=true, which rewrites text files to CRLF in the working tree.
# macos/terminal/.gitattributes already made this argument for one helper
# script -- but install.sh and uninstall.sh, the two files a stranger actually
# runs, sat one directory up with no protection at all. A CRLF install.sh
# reaching a Mac (by zip, or by copying a Windows working tree rather than
# cloning) fails with:
#     zsh: ./install.sh: bad interpreter: /bin/bash^M
# and the re-exec guard at the top of the file cannot help: the kernel is
# looking for an interpreter literally named "/bin/bash\r". Even `bash
# install.sh` then dies on `set -o errexit\r` ("invalid option name"), and
# every <<'APPLESCRIPT' / <<'JXA' heredoc would carry a trailing CR into
# osascript, so the wallpaper, the icon and the read-back verification would
# all fail at once.
#
# Scoped to macos/ on purpose: the Windows side of the repo (install.ps1, the
# Windows Terminal scheme, the FancyZones layouts) keeps its own behaviour.
#
# After adding or changing this file:  git add --renormalize macos/
# Verify with:  git ls-files --eol -- macos/     (must show w/lf)

*.sh               text eol=lf
*.md               text eol=lf
*.json             text eol=lf
*.alfredappearance text eol=lf
*.toml             text eol=lf
*.lua              text eol=lf
*.conf             text eol=lf
*.ghostty          text eol=lf
*.itermcolors      text eol=lf
*.txt              text eol=lf
*.terminal         text eol=lf

*.icns binary
*.png  binary
